1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,840
 Hello, and welcome to Web Applications for Everybody.

2
00:00:02,840 --> 00:00:06,360
 We are taking a look today at Cascading Style Sheets.

3
00:00:06,360 --> 00:00:10,280
 You can download the source code and unzip it on your computer,

4
00:00:10,280 --> 00:00:13,960
 if you like, or you can browse this code

5
00:00:13,960 --> 00:00:16,720
 and just play with it in the browser,

6
00:00:16,720 --> 00:00:19,240
 because it's all static content.

7
00:00:19,240 --> 00:00:21,400
 So it's just as easy to play with it in the browser.

8
00:00:21,400 --> 00:00:23,360
 And of course, we're going to want

9
00:00:23,360 --> 00:00:27,040
 to take a look at this in the Developer Console.

10
00:00:27,040 --> 00:00:31,840
 It just makes a lot more sense to get into this.

11
00:00:31,840 --> 00:00:34,080
 And so here we go.

12
00:00:34,080 --> 00:00:36,280
 We're taking a look at CSS.

13
00:00:36,280 --> 00:00:38,280
 There's a couple of ways to do this.

14
00:00:38,280 --> 00:00:41,800
 We can see here, we can see the style attribute.

15
00:00:41,800 --> 00:00:43,320
 Style color equals blue.

16
00:00:43,320 --> 00:00:47,640
 And there's all kinds of various CSS parameters.

17
00:00:47,640 --> 00:00:50,360
 Color is the parameter, and blue is one of the values.

18
00:00:50,360 --> 00:00:52,640
 And you've got to look all these things up.

19
00:00:52,640 --> 00:00:54,800
 One of the nice things that we can see

20
00:00:54,800 --> 00:00:59,440
 is we can see over here, as we move between elements

21
00:00:59,440 --> 00:01:03,560
 in the document object model, we can see what the CSS values are.

22
00:01:03,560 --> 00:01:06,920
 And so Arial Sans-- like, for example, this is Cascading.

23
00:01:06,920 --> 00:01:11,880
 The body on here is Arial or Sans Serif.

24
00:01:11,880 --> 00:01:14,240
 And that means that Arial font, if we can get it,

25
00:01:14,240 --> 00:01:17,080
 Sans Serif is a fallback font.

26
00:01:17,080 --> 00:01:20,320
 And so this h1, this little bit right here,

27
00:01:20,320 --> 00:01:23,840
 this h1 is being colored.

28
00:01:23,840 --> 00:01:26,080
 This is ours.

29
00:01:26,080 --> 00:01:27,560
 Browsers have their own default.

30
00:01:27,560 --> 00:01:30,560
 So display block, font size 2em, which

31
00:01:30,560 --> 00:01:33,640
 is twice as big as the rest of the font, et cetera, et cetera.

32
00:01:33,640 --> 00:01:36,440
 And so this came from the browser.

33
00:01:36,440 --> 00:01:38,680
 And then this came from the style sheet.

34
00:01:38,680 --> 00:01:41,320
 So this is Cascading.

35
00:01:41,320 --> 00:01:43,000
 And the bottom ones here are--

36
00:01:43,000 --> 00:01:44,920
 I mean, this is the most important one,

37
00:01:44,920 --> 00:01:46,880
 because this is the one we said that's closest.

38
00:01:46,880 --> 00:01:48,240
 And that's how the Cascading works.

39
00:01:51,760 --> 00:01:54,720
 There, you saw that.

40
00:01:54,720 --> 00:01:56,800
 There, you saw that.

41
00:01:56,800 --> 00:01:58,440
 And then the Cascading is--

42
00:01:58,440 --> 00:02:01,320
 again, we take a look at this little guy here, right here.

43
00:02:01,320 --> 00:02:05,440
 And so the closest one is we want a monospace font family.

44
00:02:05,440 --> 00:02:08,280
 But the body said the font family is Arial and Sans Serif.

45
00:02:08,280 --> 00:02:09,800
 But this one has been overridden.

46
00:02:09,800 --> 00:02:11,080
 And we can kind of see that.

47
00:02:11,080 --> 00:02:15,000
 And that's why this particular text is monospace.

48
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:17,120
 Another thing we can do is we put border style.

49
00:02:17,120 --> 00:02:18,680
 Now, when I'm working with this stuff,

50
00:02:18,680 --> 00:02:21,040
 I tend to remember border a lot, because it's

51
00:02:21,040 --> 00:02:23,440
 a good way for you to mark something out and say,

52
00:02:23,440 --> 00:02:24,520
 what am I doing here?

53
00:02:24,520 --> 00:02:26,840
 And we'll see when we're moving text around--

54
00:02:26,840 --> 00:02:31,160
 border, solid border, a red border, and a five pixel border.

55
00:02:31,160 --> 00:02:32,480
 And so that's what we see.

56
00:02:32,480 --> 00:02:36,160
 And you can also see that there's some extra padding

57
00:02:36,160 --> 00:02:40,840
 around there as well, or some extra margin.

58
00:02:40,840 --> 00:02:42,480
 And margin top, that's another one.

59
00:02:42,480 --> 00:02:44,240
 I'm going to scroll this up a bit.

60
00:02:44,240 --> 00:02:49,440
 Margin top throws five m's of space above the text.

61
00:02:49,440 --> 00:02:51,320
 And so this is a normal paragraph.

62
00:02:51,320 --> 00:02:52,760
 We've got five extra m's.

63
00:02:52,760 --> 00:02:53,880
 Now, what's an m?

64
00:02:53,880 --> 00:02:56,160
 m is the height of a character in the current font.

65
00:02:56,160 --> 00:02:57,960
 And so m's is a really convenient measure.

66
00:02:57,960 --> 00:03:00,760
 There's m's and pixels and percent.

67
00:03:00,760 --> 00:03:03,960
 So margin before, that's one m over here.

68
00:03:03,960 --> 00:03:05,680
 The paragraph already has an m.

69
00:03:05,680 --> 00:03:09,960
 Margin before.

70
00:03:09,960 --> 00:03:12,960
 And then-- hang on, come down here.

71
00:03:12,960 --> 00:03:15,520
 Down here, we've added the margin top.

72
00:03:15,520 --> 00:03:18,360
 So this margin top overrode the margin top

73
00:03:18,360 --> 00:03:23,360
 that was part of the paragraph tag automatically.

74
00:03:23,360 --> 00:03:25,360
 So that's these style rules.

75
00:03:25,360 --> 00:03:28,800
 So let's keep on going.

76
00:03:28,800 --> 00:03:30,480
 While this is technically possible,

77
00:03:30,480 --> 00:03:32,160
 this would really be overwhelming

78
00:03:32,160 --> 00:03:34,180
 to put a style on every tag.

79
00:03:34,180 --> 00:03:35,720
 And so one of the things we tend to do

80
00:03:35,720 --> 00:03:39,200
 is we want to put style rules that are generic.

81
00:03:39,200 --> 00:03:41,880
 So we'll say we would like the body tag.

82
00:03:41,880 --> 00:03:42,960
 And this is a style rule.

83
00:03:42,960 --> 00:03:46,240
 This is a selector, body, and then font family.

84
00:03:46,240 --> 00:03:49,400
 And again, font family works is please give me the ariel font.

85
00:03:49,400 --> 00:03:53,160
 And if that's not available, give me sans-serif font.

86
00:03:53,160 --> 00:03:56,000
 Curly brace, curly brace, h1 tags.

87
00:03:56,000 --> 00:03:57,580
 We want to go through the whole document

88
00:03:57,580 --> 00:03:59,560
 and paint h1 tags blue.

89
00:03:59,560 --> 00:04:01,240
 Go through the whole document.

90
00:04:01,240 --> 00:04:02,000
 Whole document.

91
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:03,400
 Find every paragraph tag.

92
00:04:03,400 --> 00:04:05,920
 Set the border style to solid, border color to red, five

93
00:04:05,920 --> 00:04:06,720
 pixels.

94
00:04:06,720 --> 00:04:08,040
 So you see that.

95
00:04:08,040 --> 00:04:09,000
 Every paragraph.

96
00:04:09,000 --> 00:04:10,880
 And we're going to change our anchor tags

97
00:04:10,880 --> 00:04:13,480
 to have green and have no text decoration,

98
00:04:13,480 --> 00:04:17,920
 because they're defaulted by to have--

99
00:04:17,920 --> 00:04:19,680
 they're defaulted to have underscore.

100
00:04:19,680 --> 00:04:21,360
 And we're going to make the background color light gray.

101
00:04:21,360 --> 00:04:21,720
 Why?

102
00:04:21,720 --> 00:04:22,560
 Just so we see it.

103
00:04:22,560 --> 00:04:25,400
 So you can see that particular thing up there.

104
00:04:25,400 --> 00:04:29,240
 And then if you look down into the text here,

105
00:04:29,240 --> 00:04:32,920
 we have paragraph tags and an anchor tag.

106
00:04:32,920 --> 00:04:34,720
 And no style equals down here.

107
00:04:34,720 --> 00:04:36,240
 So what we've done--

108
00:04:36,240 --> 00:04:37,560
 ignore that little part there.

109
00:04:37,560 --> 00:04:39,520
 That's what puts this little thing in the corner.

110
00:04:39,520 --> 00:04:42,120
 So that's not what we're talking about.

111
00:04:42,120 --> 00:04:44,080
 We put no style tags whatsoever.

112
00:04:44,080 --> 00:04:46,280
 And we put all the style tags up here.

113
00:04:46,280 --> 00:04:47,680
 But now we've also done something

114
00:04:47,680 --> 00:04:49,360
 that all the paragraphs have to have

115
00:04:49,360 --> 00:04:51,720
 the same style, which sometimes is what you want.

116
00:04:51,720 --> 00:04:53,400
 And sometimes it's not what you want.

117
00:04:53,400 --> 00:04:55,920
 Now what happens again now, if you have multiple pages,

118
00:04:55,920 --> 00:04:58,400
 as we have here, it gets a little tiresome

119
00:04:58,400 --> 00:05:00,720
 to put this text in every page.

120
00:05:00,720 --> 00:05:03,520
 And so what's really common instead--

121
00:05:03,520 --> 00:05:06,880
 so now we have the same basic rough paragraph stuff here.

122
00:05:06,880 --> 00:05:08,160
 Nothing in here.

123
00:05:08,160 --> 00:05:10,840
 We have a pre-tag, of course.

124
00:05:10,840 --> 00:05:12,280
 We have a paragraph tag.

125
00:05:12,280 --> 00:05:14,800
 There's no style equals on these things.

126
00:05:14,800 --> 00:05:17,560
 But up in the head, we have one line right here

127
00:05:17,560 --> 00:05:21,680
 that basically says, let's take a look at this style sheet.

128
00:05:21,680 --> 00:05:26,320
 And if we were to look at the style sheet.css,

129
00:05:26,320 --> 00:05:33,800
 it is in the same folder, rules.css.

130
00:05:33,800 --> 00:05:36,560
 It's in the same folder as that HTML file.

131
00:05:36,560 --> 00:05:38,240
 And it's exactly the stuff we had there.

132
00:05:38,240 --> 00:05:42,040
 It's just a set of selectors and then a select of key values

133
00:05:42,040 --> 00:05:45,080
 and what we want, color blue, border style, border color,

134
00:05:45,080 --> 00:05:46,760
 et cetera, et cetera, et cetera.

135
00:05:46,760 --> 00:05:52,280
 And so it really is the same as what we showed before,

136
00:05:52,280 --> 00:05:55,840
 except now that we have to put this into every file.

137
00:05:55,840 --> 00:05:58,400
 And you'll see we'll put this now from now on in every one

138
00:05:58,400 --> 00:06:01,160
 that I'm looking at.

139
00:06:01,160 --> 00:06:03,720
 And so but now our problem is that we've

140
00:06:03,720 --> 00:06:06,920
 done something with this to do all the headers, right?

141
00:06:06,920 --> 00:06:08,560
 All h1s, all paragraphs.

142
00:06:08,560 --> 00:06:11,520
 But we need better ways to mark text.

143
00:06:11,520 --> 00:06:17,320
 And so we have these tags.

144
00:06:17,320 --> 00:06:22,560
 And these tags that we use just to put handles on.

145
00:06:22,560 --> 00:06:27,160
 And in the old days, like this paragraph tag has this border.

146
00:06:27,160 --> 00:06:31,440
 See that has the margin up there?

147
00:06:31,440 --> 00:06:35,920
 I mean, it has the border, but it has this 1m margin.

148
00:06:35,920 --> 00:06:37,880
 That's that space that you're seeing

149
00:06:37,880 --> 00:06:39,160
 that makes paragraphs look good.

150
00:06:39,160 --> 00:06:42,000
 I mean, it's not a bad thing.

151
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:47,720
 And so if you look at that, we have all these colors.

152
00:06:47,720 --> 00:06:48,880
 We've got the strong tag.

153
00:06:48,880 --> 00:06:54,200
 By default, the thing uses serif font.

154
00:06:54,200 --> 00:06:57,040
 I don't like that.

155
00:06:57,040 --> 00:06:59,320
 So let's get down to here.

156
00:06:59,320 --> 00:07:05,800
 And let's just look at it here.

157
00:07:05,800 --> 00:07:09,200
 The span tag, inspect element right there.

158
00:07:09,200 --> 00:07:11,960
 OK, so the first thing is the span tag

159
00:07:11,960 --> 00:07:15,240
 is an inline tag that has no styling.

160
00:07:15,240 --> 00:07:18,640
 The problem is before CSS, which is a long time ago,

161
00:07:18,640 --> 00:07:21,160
 all these tags had default styling.

162
00:07:21,160 --> 00:07:24,640
 But the span tag is an inline tag with absolutely no styling

163
00:07:24,640 --> 00:07:25,640
 whatsoever.

164
00:07:25,640 --> 00:07:29,280
 And then the div tag is a block tag

165
00:07:29,280 --> 00:07:30,760
 that has no styling whatsoever.

166
00:07:30,760 --> 00:07:31,920
 And it can be nested.

167
00:07:31,920 --> 00:07:33,760
 So it's kind of like a paragraph tag.

168
00:07:33,760 --> 00:07:36,000
 But it has no styling whatsoever.

169
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:38,040
 Now I've added a one pixel style.

170
00:07:38,040 --> 00:07:39,760
 And you'll see that these div tags

171
00:07:39,760 --> 00:07:41,080
 don't have any extra space.

172
00:07:41,080 --> 00:07:43,720
 Like the paragraph tags came with space.

173
00:07:43,720 --> 00:07:45,440
 Now some people would go and turn off

174
00:07:45,440 --> 00:07:47,240
 the space on a paragraph tag.

175
00:07:47,240 --> 00:07:48,840
 And there's even CSS files that you

176
00:07:48,840 --> 00:07:54,200
 can to take all the styling default styling off tags.

177
00:07:54,200 --> 00:07:56,480
 But you'll notice these divs don't have any space.

178
00:07:56,480 --> 00:07:59,160
 They're really kind of a block.

179
00:07:59,160 --> 00:08:01,360
 When I put these pixel on, you see the border.

180
00:08:01,360 --> 00:08:02,800
 If you look really close, you'll see

181
00:08:02,800 --> 00:08:04,880
 that there is a one pixel blue line

182
00:08:04,880 --> 00:08:09,480
 and a one pixel orange or santa line right there.

183
00:08:09,480 --> 00:08:11,480
 But the divs can be nested.

184
00:08:11,480 --> 00:08:14,080
 And they don't themselves start.

185
00:08:14,080 --> 00:08:15,680
 So you'll notice that here they don't

186
00:08:15,680 --> 00:08:19,080
 start with any kind of formatting

187
00:08:19,080 --> 00:08:20,320
 that comes from the browser.

188
00:08:20,320 --> 00:08:22,200
 Whereas if we look at paragraphs,

189
00:08:22,200 --> 00:08:24,200
 there is formatting that comes from the browser.

190
00:08:24,200 --> 00:08:29,800
 And so the div tag and span tag are just

191
00:08:29,800 --> 00:08:33,240
 our ways to put handles around blocks of text or chunks

192
00:08:33,240 --> 00:08:35,800
 of text and then style those.

193
00:08:35,800 --> 00:08:41,320
 But then we still have to figure out how to grab our handles

194
00:08:41,320 --> 00:08:46,120
 and make it so that our styling doesn't just touch one thing.

195
00:08:46,120 --> 00:08:49,160
 And so here I've got a couple of things.

196
00:08:49,160 --> 00:08:51,080
 I've got the body tag.

197
00:08:51,080 --> 00:08:52,360
 And I'm setting font family.

198
00:08:52,360 --> 00:08:54,240
 You'll see me do this all the time.

199
00:08:54,240 --> 00:08:56,760
 And now I have a pound sign.

200
00:08:56,760 --> 00:08:59,040
 And this says go find all the tags named body.

201
00:08:59,040 --> 00:09:02,680
 This says go find all the tags with a attribute of first ID

202
00:09:02,680 --> 00:09:07,320
 equals first, ID equals second, and then class and shout.

203
00:09:07,320 --> 00:09:09,640
 So if we take a look at the text,

204
00:09:09,640 --> 00:09:13,640
 there is the notion of an ID tag.

205
00:09:13,640 --> 00:09:16,800
 An ID tag that is unique within the document.

206
00:09:16,800 --> 00:09:19,440
 So we're going to call this div first.

207
00:09:19,440 --> 00:09:21,600
 We're going to call this div second and this div third.

208
00:09:21,600 --> 00:09:25,960
 And they correspond to first, second, and third.

209
00:09:25,960 --> 00:09:31,680
 And so first is monospace.

210
00:09:31,680 --> 00:09:32,120
 What is it?

211
00:09:32,120 --> 00:09:33,640
 First is monospace.

212
00:09:33,640 --> 00:09:37,520
 Second is green.

213
00:09:37,520 --> 00:09:39,720
 So everything that's in this block that's second

214
00:09:39,720 --> 00:09:42,880
 has been green.

215
00:09:42,880 --> 00:09:45,360
 But you can only have one ID name first.

216
00:09:45,360 --> 00:09:47,200
 But class you can have all over the place.

217
00:09:47,200 --> 00:09:53,640
 So we can put the more space class

218
00:09:53,640 --> 00:09:56,120
 in a couple of different tags.

219
00:09:56,120 --> 00:09:59,800
 So this tag more space, all more space does

220
00:09:59,800 --> 00:10:02,640
 is shove it in from the left and the right.

221
00:10:02,640 --> 00:10:04,560
 Margin left and margin right.

222
00:10:04,560 --> 00:10:06,520
 So it kind of pushes this in.

223
00:10:06,520 --> 00:10:08,600
 And so you can put this on here.

224
00:10:08,600 --> 00:10:09,920
 You can put it in another place.

225
00:10:09,920 --> 00:10:15,280
 And so the more space pulls in something here.

226
00:10:15,280 --> 00:10:17,960
 So here's another paragraph that's got more space.

227
00:10:17,960 --> 00:10:19,240
 That one has more space.

228
00:10:19,240 --> 00:10:20,320
 This one has more space.

229
00:10:20,320 --> 00:10:21,680
 See that one?

230
00:10:21,680 --> 00:10:24,720
 And so you can put more space on as many times as you like.

231
00:10:24,720 --> 00:10:26,040
 And then div third.

232
00:10:26,040 --> 00:10:38,200
 And so the hierarchical section means, in this case,

233
00:10:38,200 --> 00:10:40,040
 this one's a little bit-- and loud is red.

234
00:10:40,040 --> 00:10:41,160
 So where's loud at?

235
00:10:41,160 --> 00:10:44,680
 Let's inspect that one.

236
00:10:44,680 --> 00:10:46,680
 Inspect element.

237
00:10:46,680 --> 00:10:50,040
 So that's a-- and this loud is not only red,

238
00:10:50,040 --> 00:10:51,920
 but it's also forced uppercase.

239
00:10:51,920 --> 00:10:55,360
 Text transform to uppercase.

240
00:10:55,360 --> 00:10:56,360
 Shouting and loud.

241
00:10:56,360 --> 00:11:03,000
 And you can have more than one class on a tag.

242
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:07,760
 And then you can be even more precise with your selection.

243
00:11:07,760 --> 00:11:12,440
 This is basically-- this says, find a third ID.

244
00:11:12,440 --> 00:11:15,720
 And then only paragraphs within that tag third

245
00:11:15,720 --> 00:11:18,320
 make their background color yellow.

246
00:11:18,320 --> 00:11:20,520
 And so that means that background color yellow

247
00:11:20,520 --> 00:11:22,040
 does not apply to this tag.

248
00:11:22,040 --> 00:11:23,720
 It doesn't apply to this paragraph.

249
00:11:23,720 --> 00:11:25,760
 Doesn't apply to this paragraph.

250
00:11:25,760 --> 00:11:27,720
 But when you see div ID third, we

251
00:11:27,720 --> 00:11:31,360
 have selected this paragraph and this paragraph.

252
00:11:31,360 --> 00:11:34,840
 And they have a background color of yellow.

253
00:11:34,840 --> 00:11:36,800
 So continuing on, let's take a look

254
00:11:36,800 --> 00:11:39,040
 at a simple navigation bar.

255
00:11:39,040 --> 00:11:42,640
 Now, there's this nav tag that's an HTML5 thing.

256
00:11:42,640 --> 00:11:45,000
 And if you look at most navigation on pages--

257
00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:47,160
 let's go to the next one.

258
00:11:47,160 --> 00:11:48,920
 They're pretty, and they got colors,

259
00:11:48,920 --> 00:11:51,000
 and they move around and stuff.

260
00:11:51,000 --> 00:11:54,920
 But we want to be careful when we build our HTML

261
00:11:54,920 --> 00:11:58,560
 for these kinds of things to make them very, very simple.

262
